        <definition>XVprocSs_Config* XVprocSs_LookupConfig</definition>
        <argsstring>(UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>XVprocSs_LookupConfig</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function looks for the device configuration based on the unique device ID. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The table XVprocSs_ConfigTable[] contains the configuration information for each instance of the device in the system.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>DeviceId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the unique device ID of the device being looked up</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the configuration table entry corresponding to the given device ID, or NULL if no match is found This function searches for and returns a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_vproc_ss___config" kindref="compound">XVprocSs_Config</ref> structure that matches the specified BaseAddress. If BaseAddress is zero, it returns the first entry in the XVprocSs_ConfigTable. If no matching configuration is found, it returns NULL.</para></simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the base address of the device to look up.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the matching <ref refid="struct_x_vproc_ss___config" kindref="compound">XVprocSs_Config</ref> structure if found, otherwise NULL. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
